        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Sir Anthony Hopkins was a relative unknown when he took on the role of Bruno Richard Hauptmann in Columbia Pictures' 1976 "The Lindbergh Kidnapping Case."  Hopkins won an Emmy for his performance. Sensational headlines and speculative journalism in William Randolph Hurst's newspapers made it difficult to find an unbiased jury.The Lindbergh kidnapping was the subject of a second film, 1998's "The Crime of the Century," a phrase reputedly coined by newspaper reporter Damon Runyon.</description>
